# Unit tests (this repository)

When adding or editing unit tests, follow these rules.

## Layout

- Put tests in **`__tests__`** next to the module under test (e.g. `src/.../book/__tests__/book.entity.test.ts`).
- Use `*.test.ts`. Keep `vitest.config.ts` `include` aligned with `src/**/__tests__/**/*.test.ts`.

## Gherkin structure

- **`describe`**: only **Given** and **When**. One string per block = keyword + full sentence (e.g. `Given I have…`, `When I register…`).
- **`it`**: every **Then** — title must start with **`Then`** and describe the outcome in **domain** terms (ubiquitous language, user/librarian perspective). No `describe` for Then-only groups.

## Style

- Prefer library/domain wording over internal jargon in titles unless the test is intentionally low-level.
- Shared setup lives under **Given** (`beforeEach` when several **Then** cases need the same fresh state).

## Imports

- From `__tests__`, import the subject with a relative path up one level (e.g. `../book.entity`).
